OUTSIDE ORGANISATION: MK FIRE LTD (ON BEHALF OF SALVATION ARMY)

DETAILS:

Grant arrived at around 8.30 where he presented documentation to Jem as she left the building. After being let in Fahad accompanied him in his inspection around the building as they checked each kitchen for fire blankets and extinguishers.
GRANT‰ÛªS CONCERNS:

It was worrying to myself to hear about the concerns raised by Grant as we walked through the building. Considering the door stop ban it is extremely worrying that a professional voiced his doubts about the building. Suggesting that while the coverage is legal it may not be effective.

column2: Fire extinguishers not found in corridors
In some kitchens only a fire blanket can be found
30-40 extinguishers have been found in the basement

column1: With respect to the last point it seems illogical for DDD to have removed the extinguishers from the corridors only to leave them in the kitchens. Should DD have removed them due to untrained guardians being the obvious user why would the extinguishers remain in kitchens?
Grant will be voicing his concerns to Louise later on today.
GUARDIAN ACTIONS:

column2: Request a copy of the fire risk assessment

column1: After liaising with a college of his Grant confirmed to myself that as each escape has an extinguisher DDD are compliant with fire regulation. However, in his professional opinion the corridors are too long for the extinguishers to provide any real coverage. The above action appears to be the only way that guardians can find out who is liable should the worst occur.
CLOSING COMMENTS:

Considering the recent fire issues in London and the fact that our building is respectively old, I believe that this is a cause for concern for Guardians. I would like to note however that Grant was extremely impressed with the time and dedication that has been invested in the building and the level of trust exhibited between guardians as he cited that many people leave their rooms unlocked. [04/11/2019, 09:33:05] ‰Û»+44åÊ7717åÊ345724‰ÛÂ: Dungeons and Dragons is the original tabletop role playing game.  Think of it like a choose your own adventure crossed with improv.  You create a character from Tolkienesque species (i.e. I'm dragonborn, Anya's half-Orc, you can also be human) with certain skills.  You can create a whole backstory and personality which determine how you behave in the adventure.  The Dungeon Master is basically the storyteller, explaining where you are, what you see, and the results of your actions.  You use dice to determine if you're successful or unsuccessful in your choices.
